ral`"},"760":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-42","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#emphasis","content":"Subtle, low-emphasis label"},"761":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-43","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#sizes","content":"Choose a size that fits the surrounding content. Smaller tags work well in compact layouts like tables; larger tags suit headings or hero sections."},"762":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-44","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#inline","content":"Use `design=\"inline\"` to embed a tag within a sentence. The background and border are removed so the tag blends into the text flow."},"763":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-45","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#high-contrast","content":"A bolder color treatment for when tags need to stand out more — for example, on colored backgrounds."},"764":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-46","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#with-icon","content":"Icons reinforce the tag's meaning at a glance. Add an `Icon` as a child — it inherits the tag's color and scales with its size."},"765":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-47","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#indicator","content":"A minimal style that uses a small colored dot instead of a full background. Useful in tables or dashboards where too many colors would be distracting."},"766":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-48","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"The `design` prop controls the visual treatment:"},"767":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-49","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"`design`"},"768":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-50","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"What it looks like"},"769":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-51","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"Best for"},"770":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-52","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"`filled`"},"771":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-53","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"Colored background with contrasting text"},"772":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-54","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"Most use cases"},"773":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-55","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"`inline`"},"774":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-56","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"Text only, no background or border"},"775":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-57","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"Inside paragraphs or sentences"},"776":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-58","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#design-modes","content":"> **Indicator** is a separate boolean prop (`indicator={true}`), not a `design` value. It renders a colored dot on a plain background and forces high-contrast colors — useful in tables and data-heavy views. See the Indicator example above."},"777":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-59","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#screen-readers","content":"Tags are `<span>` elements with no special ARIA role. Screen readers announce the tag's text as part of normal page content — no extra markup is needed."},"778":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-60","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#decorative-icons","content":"Icons passed as children must include `aria-hidden=\"true\"` so they are skipped by screen readers. The text label is the sole carrier of meaning."},"779":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-61","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#indicator-dot","content":"The colored dot is a CSS `::before` pseudo-element with no text content. It is invisible to screen readers by design. The text label must convey the status on its own."},"780":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-62","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Use `indicator` for dense layouts (tables, dashboards) where a full colored background would be distracting. Reserve `filled` for prominent placements like cards or hero sections."},"781":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-63","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Always mark decorative icons with `aria-hidden=\"true\"` — the text label carries the meaning, not the icon."},"782":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-64","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Default to `size=\"sm\"` in tables and compact lists. Step up to `md` or `lg` only when the tag is a primary visual element."},"783":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-65","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Use `design=\"inline\"` only within running text. Avoid it in standalone or grouped tag contexts where the background provides useful visual separation."},"784":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-66","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Do not combine multiple tags of different emphasis on the same item. Choose the most important one — stacking emphasis dilutes all of them."},"785":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-67","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Showing status on a card or list item (e.g. \"Active\", \"Expired\")"},"786":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-68","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Categorizing content (e.g. \"New\", \"Sale\", \"Beta\")"},"787":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-69","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Displaying metadata labels (e.g. \"Pro\", \"Free trial\")"},"788":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-70","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-not-to-use","content":"If users need to click or dismiss it — use a **Chip** or **Button** instead."},"789":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-71","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-not-to-use","content":"If you need a number count — use a **Badge**."},"790":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-72","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-not-to-use","content":"If the label is part of a sentence with no visual distinction — just use text."},"791":{"id":"/docs/components/text","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"page","content":"Text","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text"},"792":{"id":"/docs/components/text-0","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text","content":"Text component for displaying and formatting text content with alignment and truncation options"},"793":{"id":"/docs/components/text-1","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#installation","content":"Installation"},"794":{"id":"/docs/components/text-2","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#props","content":"Props"},"795":{"id":"/docs/components/text-3","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#examples","content":"Examples"},"796":{"id":"/docs/components/text-4","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#as","content":"As"},"797":{"id":"/docs/components/text-5","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#align","content":"Align"},"798":{"id":"/docs/components/text-6","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#max-lines","content":"Max Lines"},"799":{"id":"/docs/components/text-7","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"Wrap"},"800":{"id":"/docs/components/text-8","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text","content":"The `Text` component prepares content with a few properties."},"801":{"id":"/docs/components/text-9","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#props","content":"The `Text` component accepts the following props:"},"802":{"id":"/docs/components/text-10","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#as","content":"Setting the `as` prop allows you to change the HTML tag of the `Text` component."},"803":{"id":"/docs/components/text-11","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#align","content":"Setting the `align` prop allows you to change the alignment of the text. You can choose from `start`, `center`, `end`, or `justify`.\n`start` works like `left` and `end` works like `right`. These keywords support RTL languages so you do not need to worry about the language of the text."},"804":{"id":"/docs/components/text-12","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#max-lines","content":"Setting the `maxLines` prop allows you to limit the number of lines of text that are displayed using an ellipsis. In browsers that don't support multiline text truncation using `line-clamp`, the text will be truncated after a single line regardless of the number provided for `maxLines`."},"805":{"id":"/docs/components/text-13","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"Setting the `wrap` prop allows you to change the wrapping of the text. The values can be `wrap`, `nowrap`, `balance`, `pretty`, or `stable`."},"806":{"id":"/docs/components/text-14","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`wrap` is the setting that is most commonly used. For most elements you will not to explicitly set this."},"807":{"id":"/docs/components/text-15","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`nowrap` should be avoided except in cases where it is important to prevent the text from wrapping."},"808":{"id":"/docs/components/text-16","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`balance` is most commonly used for headlines, titles, and labels."},"809":{"id":"/docs/components/text-17","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`pretty` is most commonly used for body text."},"810":{"id":"/docs/components/text-18","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`stable` is commonly used for editable text, such as textareas."},"811":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"page","content":"TextField","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field"},"812":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-0","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field","content":"TextField is a single-line or multiline text input with optional label, description, and error message. Use it in forms for short answers (email, search, name) or longer content (comments). It supports optional leading and trailing text adornments (e.g. currency or units)."},"813":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-1","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#features","content":"Features"},"814":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-2","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#installation","content":"Installation"},"815":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-3","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#props","content":"Props"},"816":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-4","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#examples","content":"Examples"},"817":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-5","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#basic","content":"Basic"},"818":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-6","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#controlled","content":"Controlled"},"819":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-7","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#invalid","content":"Invalid"},"820":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-8","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#disabled","content":"Disabled"},"821":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-9","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#adornments","content":"Adornments"},"822":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-10","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field#multiline","content":"Multiline"},"823":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-11","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#features","content":"**Label, description, error**: Optional label, helper text, and error message with proper accessibility"},"824":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-12","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#features","content":"**Adornments**: Optional `leadingText` and `trailingText` for fixed text before or after the input (e.g. `$`, `.00`, `px`)"},"825":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-13","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#features","content":"**Controlled or uncontrolled**: Use `value` and `onChange` for controlled state, or `defaultValue` for uncontrolled"},"826":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-14","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#features","content":"**Multiline**: Set `multiline` to render a textarea instead of a single-line input"},"827":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-15","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#features","content":"**Validation states**: Use `isInvalid` with `errorMessage` and `isDisabled` for validation and disabled state"},"828":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-16","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#features","content":"**React Aria integration**: Built on React Aria TextField for accessibility and behavior"},"829":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-17","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#props","content":"The TextField component accepts the following props:"},"830":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-18","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#basic","content":"Minimal usage with label and placeholder."},"831":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-19","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#controlled","content":"Use `value` and `onChange` for controlled state."},"832":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-20","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#invalid","content":"Use `isInvalid` with `errorMessage` for validation feedback."},"833":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-21","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#disabled","content":"Use `isDisabled` to prevent input."},"834":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-22","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#adornments","content":"Use `leadingText` and `trailingText` for fixed text before and after the input (e.g. currency)."},"835":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-23","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field#multiline","content":"Use `multiline` to render a textarea."},"836":{"id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","page_id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","type":"page","content":"ToggleButton","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/toggle-button"},"837":{"id":"/docs/components/toggle-button-0","page_id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/toggle-button","content":"Accessible toggle button component for grouped contextual actions with single or multiple selection, keyboard navigation, and RTL-aware layouts."},"838":{"id":"/docs/components/toggle-button-1","page_id":"/docs/components/toggle-button","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"